cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.DB 

This paper involves the use of a deep neural network for predicting readmission to the ICU based on longitudinal EMR data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of EMR data, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases). The use of attention-based models and Bayesian inference suggests that the paper could also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CY (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper involves the interpretation of the model's predictions to describe patients-at-risk, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
